Rachel BakerAfter taking Bollywood by storm with her impeccable acting chops and envious looks, Deepika Padukone is all set to work her magic in Hollywood as well.
The actress has auditioned for a pivotal role in the popular 'The Mummy' franchise opposite Hollywood heartthrob, Tom Cruise.
| TNN | May 5, 2016, 10.27 AM ISTDeepika PadukoneAfter taking Bollywood by storm with her impeccable acting chops and envious looks, B-Town hottie, Deepika Padukone is all set to work her magic in Hollywood as well.While the actress is busy shooting for her Hollywood debut 'xXx: The Return of Xander Cage' opposite Vin Diesel in Canada, we hear that the leggy lass has been auditioning for few other roles while being away from home.
According to a report on Spotboye.com, the 'Goliyon Ki Rasleela Ram-Leela' actress has auditioned for a pivotal role in the popular 'The Mummy' franchise opposite Hollywood heartthrob, Tom Cruise.
The report states that Deepika had auditioned sometime last month and is still waiting for a revert from the casting directors.
However, the casting directors have now been looking for other prospects for the role, added the report.
A few days ago, reports were doing the rounds that 'Gangs of Wasseypur' actress Huma Qureshi had also auditioned for the said role.
So will it be Deepika or Huma opposite Tom Cruise?
